From a microscopic perspective, the adhesion force between the coating and substrate depends on the contact strength of the interface. A fundamental quantity determining the strength of the interface is the ideal work of the adhesion (Wad), which is the work spent on separating the interface into two free surface. The work of adhesion between the coating and substrate can be calculated using Eq. (4) [33, 34]:4Wad=(Eslab1+Eslab2-Eint)/A,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
